    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="man_ej.00023.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place" rend="center"><handShift rend="printed"/>Asylum for the Insane,</name>
                    <name type="place" rend="right">London,</name>
                    <date when="1880-02-03" rend="right"><handShift rend="manuscript"/><choice><abbr>Feb</abbr><expan>February</expan></choice> 3<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> <handShift rend="printed"/>18<handShift rend="manuscript"/>80</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My dear Walt</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I have Burrough's book and also his last article in "Birds &#38; Poets". I have O'Connor's "Good Gray Poet" parts of which are <choice><sic>beautifull</sic><corr>beautiful</corr></choice>&#8212;I have Mrs. <choice><sic>Gilchrists</sic><corr>Gilchrist's</corr></choice> letter in the "Radical."<ptr target="man.00003_n1"/> All these and <hi rend="underline">anything</hi> else I can get on this subject are interesting, and will be more or less <choice><sic>usefull</sic><corr>useful</corr></choice>, to me&#8212;but what I <hi rend="underline">specially</hi> want just now is new facts about the <hi rend="underline">man</hi>&#8212;both bearing upon his inward and outward life&#8212;I hope you will give me any help in <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="lozynsky">reason</unclear> that you 
                
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="man_ej.00024.jpg" type="verso"/>
            
                can in this direction.</p>
            
            <p>I hope that your brothers will do something for me and I hope that if you have any thing to say about it you will encourage them to do something<ptr target="man.00003_n2"/>&#8212;I will return the little pamphlet<ptr target="man.00003_n3"/> after awhile meantime I will take good care of it &#38; be sure not to lose it.</p>
           
            <closer>
                <salute>Yours always</salute>
                <signed rend="right">R M Bucke</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
